synopsis: Kaori writes about the time Yuki had struggled with a math problem during class and about the smile she put on his face when explaining why she likes math.
Kaori describes Shogo's seemingly cold personality but comes to understand him a little better after she asks Yuki about him.
Kaori writes about the time she had lost her diary and about how hard Yuki tried to find it.
Kaori writes about the date she had with Saki one Friday after school.
Kaori writes about the afternoon that herself, Yuki, Shogo and Saki gathered at her house to study.
Kaori writes about how she chose a present for Yuki.
Kaori writes about how she went to beach and game center with her friends.
Kaori writes about how she spent last day of summer break.
Kaori writes about how she forgot about Yuki but he seemed a nice person and she decided to write in a diary every day.
Kaori writes about the day that she remembered how started to lose memory every week. She also writes that she can be friends with new people she met at school.
Kaori writes how she was able to tell Yuki that she wanted them to be friends.
Yuki writes about how he made up with Kaori and how the memories that they made together are important to keep.
